    "sentence_rhythm": {
      "rule": "Rhythm is unpredictable by design. That unpredictability is the personality.",
      "pattern": "No fixed cadence. A short sentence lands like a fact. Then a longer one comes in and takes its time, builds something, lets the reader settle into an idea before it moves on. Then short again. The reader should never predict the next sentence's length.",
